content: I am whte, as you know
Today I will introduce an email game between mak and me.
As you know, email games are not like other games, every player has 135 days.
That means we have plenty of time to analysis every variant deeply.
So, here I want to share some of the home analysis of it.
If there is any mistake, please feel free to point it out.
Now, the game. email 2004, in group B
My opponent is a Russia top player Makarov Pavel.
Makarov Pavel opened the game, it is D3 opening.  Of course, I kept white.
The first ten moves are logical.
the same opening as we saw last time in klimatchev vs freefish
11-i7 has been introduced by Zhang Jin Yu days ago. Let's just skip it.
13-K8 block white pair and become his own pair.
Black looks very good in shape.
But white 14-G10 is a perfect move. It makes its own two pairs and control black.
This 14 gives white nearly sure win.
Do you want to test some?
Who would want to challenge as white?
I put a 15 and you say "me", and you can show the white win.
i would go on with triples
the only option of the black
strongest defense, and also the only defense.

if black defense like this, who want to try?

After 23, white has some choices. Should I use the three at f10 or not?
RT Ando told us, never use the 3 or 4 unless it is necessary.
I thought the lower side has enough space to win with the help from the left side.
But it was not enough that the left side alone had enough power to win. So I made a 24 at H6 following this idea. But later on,
But later on, I found I miscalculate something.
